            <title>[KAFKA-1147] Consumer socket timeout should be greater than fetch max wait</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1147</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From the mailing list:&lt;br/&gt;
The consumer-config documentation states that &quot;The actual timeout set&lt;br/&gt;
will be max.fetch.wait + socket.timeout.ms.&quot; - however, that change&lt;br/&gt;
seems to have been lost in the code a while ago - we should either fix the doc or re-introduce the addition.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
